            <p>Electrical conductivity of chemically pure water is very insignificant. The degree of water dissociation, calculated by measurement of electric conductivity of water, is equal to 1.8.10-9. The number of water molecules which dissociate forming ions is extremely small. The process of water electrolytic dissociation is possible as a result of high polarity of the bond O&mdash;H and the presence of hydrogen bonds between molecules of water. In water and aqueous solutions hydrogen ions H+ interact with water molecules producing hydrated protons, these are oxonium ions H3O+:<br>
