            <p>One of the most common real life examples of a redox reaction is one that is necessary for life itself, in which a cell oxidizes glucose to carbon dioxide and reduces oxygen to water, providing energy through cellular respiration. In plants, the reaction occurs in the opposite direction and uses energy supplied by the sun. <br>
