            <p>Dispersion system is a system, in which particles of one substance are spread inside another substance. That substance, which in a form of small particles is spread inside the another substance, is called the disperse phase, which serves as the medium for the other one is called dispersion medium. According to the size of disperse phase particles disperse system are divided into: <br>
